Never delet.

Do NOT delet!

Archive in a special archive that you keep separate so it may never see the light of day, if you really feel it needs to be delet. But,

Do.

NOT.

EVER.

Delet.

The day will come when you browse that horrible writing, and you will find gems in it, gems that would be lost because you did not recognize them until years later. I pass this wisdom on from one who knows this better than most will ever know. Those roughs often have a unique phrasing or raw style that came through during the original creative attempt, and then lost as you tried to polish it.

Lost forever.

Don't over-edit electronic text. Each pass you make, save it as a different copy, with naming convention and notes to help keep them separated & organized.

Have I mentioned? Don't delete shit. Listen to this wisdom. It is very nearly the First Commandment of writing.
